A small slender-stemmed palm, about 15 feet high, with pinnate leaves. Native to Brazil. For previous introduction see 104681.
A small shrub with drooping branches and rounded leaves, the two lobes rounded oval, white-hairy beneath. The small yellow flowers are in racemes of 12 to 18. Native to eastern India.

A palm, native to China, with a short thick trunk up to 6 feet high and 1 foot thick, having a crown of reniform palmately divided leaves 4 to 6 feet across on petioles about 5 feet long, which are armed below the middle with recurved brown spines more than an inch long. For previous introduction see 93412.
A slender palm about 50 feet high, with a crown of large fan-shaped leaves. It is native to Malacca. For previous introduction see 104240.
For previous introduction and description see 105448.

A Colombian tree up to 100 feet high with a large thick trunk, smooth pale bark, large shallowly five- to seven-lobed leaves, and red flowers 1 inch long. The soft coarse pithlike wood is white or yellowish and is used for making canoes and rafts. For previous introduction see 98928.

A large tropical tree, 40 to 60 feet high, with compound leaves, two to four broadly elliptic leaves, white flowers in small corymbs. Native to southern India.
Plants of a tropical tree of moderate size, with ovate or rounded thick leaves 5 or 6 inches long and fragrant white flowers, 2 inches long, in corymb-like clusters. Native to Assam, India.
An evergreen tree with alternate pinnate leaves and racemes of purplish pea-like flowers. For previous introduction see 94776.
